# FraudWatch

**AI-Powered Financial Fraud Detection & Risk Intelligence Platform**

An enterprise-grade fraud detection and risk management platform inspired by systems used at Stripe, Visa, Mastercard, PayPal, and Revolut.

## Architecture

```
FraudWatch/
├── frontend/          # Next.js 15 dashboard & client application
├── backend/           # FastAPI microservices & API layer
├── ml/                # Machine learning pipeline & models
├── docker/            # Container configurations
├── docs/              # Documentation
├── scripts/           # Deployment & utility scripts
└── .github/           # CI/CD workflows
```

## Technology Stack

### Frontend
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS + shadcn/ui
- **State**: Zustand + TanStack Query
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod
- **Charts**: Recharts
- **Icons**: Lucide React

### Backend
- **Framework**: FastAPI (Python 3.12)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 16 + SQLAlchemy 2.x
- **Migrations**: Alembic
- **Cache**: Redis 7
- **Queue**: Celery
- **Auth**: JWT + python-jose
- **Validation**: Pydantic v2

### ML Pipeline
- **Data Processing**: pandas, numpy
- **Models**: scikit-learn, XGBoost, Isolation Forest
- **Explainability**: SHAP
- **Optimization**: Optuna
- **Serialization**: Joblib

### Infrastructure
- **Containerization**: Docker + Docker Compose
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions
- **Deployment**: Vercel (frontend) + Render (backend)
- **Database**: Neon PostgreSQL
- **Cache**: Upstash Redis

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 20+
- Python 3.12+
- PostgreSQL 16+
- Redis 7+
- Docker & Docker Compose

### Development Setup

#### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-org/fraudwatch.git
cd fraudwatch
```

#### 2. Backend Setup
```bash
cd backend
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Copy environment file
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your configuration

# Run migrations
alembic upgrade head

# Start development server
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
```

#### 3. Frontend Setup
```bash
cd frontend
npm install

# Copy environment file
cp .env.example .env.local
# Edit .env.local with your configuration

# Start development server
npm run dev
```

#### 4. ML Environment Setup
```bash
cd ml
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn xgboost shap optuna joblib jupyter
```

### Docker Compose (Full Stack)

```bash
docker-compose up -d
```

Services will be available at:
- Frontend: http://localhost:3000
- Backend API: http://localhost:8000
- API Docs: http://localhost:8000/docs
- PostgreSQL: localhost:5432
- Redis: localhost:6379

## Project Structure

### Frontend (`frontend/`)
```
app/                    # Next.js App Router pages
├── (auth)/             # Authentication pages
├── (dashboard)/        # Dashboard pages
├── api/                # Next.js API routes
├── layout.tsx          # Root layout
└── page.tsx            # Landing page

components/            # Reusable components
├── layout/             # Layout components
├── charts/             # Chart components
├── tables/             # Table components
├── forms/              # Form components
├── cards/              # Card components
└── ui/                 # shadcn/ui components

hooks/                 # Custom React hooks
services/              # API service layer
stores/                # Zustand state management
lib/                   # Utility libraries
utils/                 # Helper functions
types/                 # TypeScript type definitions
constants/             # Application constants
styles/                # Global styles
```

### Backend (`backend/app/`)
```
api/
└── v1/                 # API v1 routes
    └── auth/           # Authentication endpoints

config/                 # Configuration management
core/                   # Core utilities (logging, etc.)
database/               # Database connection & session management
models/                 # SQLAlchemy ORM models (to be added)
schemas/                # Pydantic schemas (to be added)
repositories/           # Data access layer (to be added)
services/               # Business logic layer (to be added)
middleware/             # Custom middleware
workers/                # Celery background tasks
utils/                  # Utility functions
dependencies/           # FastAPI dependencies
security/               # Auth & security utilities
exceptions/             # Custom exception classes
tests/                  # Test suite
```

### ML Pipeline (`ml/`)
```
datasets/
├── raw/                # Raw data ingestion
└── processed/          # Processed datasets

notebooks/              # Jupyter notebooks for EDA
preprocessing/          # Data preprocessing scripts
feature_engineering/    # Feature engineering
training/               # Model training scripts
evaluation/             # Model evaluation
models/                 # Saved model files
artifacts/              # Model artifacts & metadata
explainability/         # SHAP explanations
pipelines/              # ML pipeline orchestration
```

